data.chText: 空白的
data.enText: empty, with nothing written, printed or recorded on it

data.chText: 把名字签在下面的空白处。
data.enText: Sign your name in the blank space below.

data.chText: 空白光盘
data.enText: a blank CD

data.chText: 写在纸的一面，把另一面空出来。
data.enText: Write on one side of the paper and leave the other side blank.

data.chText: 她翻开笔记本的一张空白页。
data.enText: She turned to a blank page in her notebook.

data.chText: 空的；无图画（或标记、装饰）的
data.enText: empty; with no pictures, marks or decoration

data.chText: 光秃秃的白灰墙
data.enText: blank whitewashed walls

data.chText: 屏幕突然变成一片空白。
data.enText: Suddenly the screen went blank .

data.chText: 没表情的；不理解的；不感兴趣的
data.enText: showing no feeling, understanding or interest

data.chText: 她木然地盯着我。
data.enText: She stared at me with a blank expression on her face.

data.chText: 史蒂夫显得很迷惑，说他不知道我在说什么。
data.enText: Steve looked blank and said he had no idea what I was talking about.

data.chText: 我脑子里突然一片空白。
data.enText: Suddenly my mind went blank (= I could not remember anything).

data.chText: 完全的；彻底的
data.enText: complete and total

data.chText: 断然拒绝 / 否认
data.enText: a blank refusal/denial

data.chText: 她两眼发直，不知道下面该说什么。
data.enText: She stared blankly into space, not knowing what to say next.

data.chText: （文件等的）空白处，空格
data.enText: an empty space on a printed form or document for you to write answers, information, etc. in

data.chText: 请在空白处填写。
data.enText: Please fill in the blanks .

data.chText: 如果回答不了问题，就空着它。
data.enText: If you can't answer the question, leave a blank.

data.chText: （记忆中的）空白，遗忘
data.enText: a state of not being able to remember anything

data.chText: 我脑子里是一片空白，记不起她的名字了。
data.enText: My mind was a blank and I couldn't remember her name.
blank cartridge

data.chText: 空弹
data.enText: a cartridge in a gun that contains an explosive but no bullet

data.chText: 部队向空中放空弹。
data.enText: The troops fired blanks in the air.
draw a blank

data.chText: 无回音；无结果；无收获
data.enText: to get no response or result

data.chText: 到目前为止警方的调查毫无结果。
data.enText: So far, the police investigation has drawn a blank.

data.chText: 毫不理睬（某人）
data.enText: to ignore sb completely

data.chText: 我今天早晨在公共汽车上见到她，但她连一眼都没瞧我。
data.enText: I saw her on the bus this morning, but she totally blanked me.

data.chText: 突然忘掉；突然思路模糊
data.enText: to be suddenly unable to remember or think of sth

data.chText: 我本来知道答案，但考试时我什么都忘了。
data.enText: I knew the answer, but I totally blanked during the test.
blank out

data.chText: 突然变空
data.enText: to suddenly become empty

data.chText: 屏幕突然变成一片空白。
data.enText: The screen blanked out.
blank sth↔out

data.chText: 掩盖；遮盖
data.enText: to cover sth completely so that it cannot be seen

data.chText: 信中所有的名字都已涂掉。
data.enText: All the names in the letter had been blanked out.

data.chText: 刻意忘记；抹去记忆
data.enText: to deliberately forget sth unpleasant

data.chText: 她曾试图把全部经历从记忆中抹去。
data.enText: She had tried to blank out the whole experience.

synonyms.bx: 指纸张无字迹的、未印刷过的，或磁带未录制内容的。

ex.chText: 她在那个空荡荡的小房间住了6年。
ex.enText: She lived in that tiny bare room for six years.

ex.chText: 她穿着一件低领连衣裙，手臂裸露。
ex.enText: She wore a low-necked dress, and her arms were bare.

ex.chText: 卧室里地板裸露，没有铺地毯。
ex.enText: There's no carpet in the bedroom, just bare floorboards.

synonyms.bx: 指建筑物内部缺乏设施或装饰的，也指人身体部位裸露的，形容土地、树木等时表示其没有植被覆盖或枝叶凋落的。

ex.chText: 这房子好多年没人住了。
ex.enText: The house stood empty for many years.

synonyms.bx: 指容器里面什么也没有或者某个地方没有人的。

ex.chText: 使用空心砖是因为它们更轻。
ex.enText: Hollow blocks are used because they are lighter.

synonyms.bx: 指实物的内部是空心的。

ex.chText: 他辞职后，这个职位暂时空缺。
ex.enText: The position became vacant after his resignation.

synonyms.bx: 指房屋、土地等未被占用的，或指工作或职位空缺的，侧重表示临时性的情况。

trans: 不再去想；刻意忘却

tr: a cartridge containing an explosive charge but no bullet
a piece of material ready to be made into something
a blank gap or missing part
a blank character used to separate successive words in writing or printing
example: he said the space is the most important character in the alphabet

tr: keep the opposing (baseball) team from winning
(of a surface) not written or printed on

value.def: Something that is blank has nothing on it.

example.ex: We could put some of the pictures over on that blank wall over there...
example.tran: 我们可以把一些图画贴在那边的空白墙壁上。

example.ex: He tore a blank page from his notebook.
example.tran: 他从他的笔记本上撕下一页空白纸。

value.def: A blank is a space which is left in a piece of writing or on a printed form for you to fill in particular information.

example.ex: Put a word in each blank to complete the sentence.
example.tran: 每个空格填上一个单词，把句子补充完整。

value.def: If you look blank, your face shows no feeling, understanding, or interest.

example.ex: Abbot looked blank. 'I don't quite follow, sir.'...
example.tran: 阿博特一脸茫然。“我没听明白，先生。”

example.ex: His daughter gave him a blank look.
example.tran: 他女儿漠然地看了他一眼。

value.tran: 茫然的；漠然的；毫无表情的

example.tran: 她面无表情地凝视着他。

example.ex: His eyes have the blankness of someone half-asleep.
example.tran: 他的眼睛透着茫然，一副半睡半醒的样子。

value.def: If your mind or memory is a blank, you cannot think of anything or remember anything.

example.ex: I'm sorry, but my mind is a blank...
example.tran: 对不起，我脑子里一片空白。

example.ex: I came round in hospital and did not know where I was. Everything was a complete blank.
example.tran: 我在医院里醒了过来，不知道自己身在何处。一切都是空白。

value.def: Blanks are gun cartridges which contain explosive but do not contain a bullet, so that they cause no harm when the gun is fired.

example.ex: ...a starter pistol which only fires blanks.
example.tran: 只发射空包弹的发令枪

value.def: If you draw a blank when you are looking for someone or something, you do not succeed in finding them.

example.ex: They drew a blank in their search for the driver.
example.tran: 他们四处寻找那个司机，但一无所获。

value.def: If your mind goes blank, you are suddenly unable to think of anything appropriate to say, for example in reply to a question.

example.tran: 我的脑子突然一片空白。
